Warren "Wazza" Ackary (born September 27, 1959) is a Australian professional darts player who currently plays in the World Seniors events and formerly of the Professional Darts Corporation (PDC) tournaments. His the nickname called Wazza.
Career
Ackary played in the 2010 PDC Pro Tour Players Championship events of Sydney, New South Wales, Australia, before losing to the preliminary round with Malaysia's Abdul Ghani Amin by 6 legs to 3..
